# Basic Authentication Protection (Optional)
# This file is optional and only works on servers with Apache and mod_auth enabled
# For GitHub Pages, use the client-side JavaScript authentication instead

# Uncomment the lines below to enable Basic Auth protection
# Note: You'll need to create a .htpasswd file with the following command:
# htpasswd -c .htpasswd gisuser
# Then enter the password: gispass

# AuthType Basic
# AuthName "GIS Viewer - Restricted Access"
# AuthUserFile /path/to/.htpasswd
# Require valid-user

# Redirect HTTP to HTTPS (optional)
# RewriteEngine On
# RewriteCond %{HTTPS} off
# RewriteRule ^(.*)$ https://%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI} [L,R=301]

